node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Instantly on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'RICHEST MAN EVER Mansa Musa was the king of TIMBUKTU and lived between 1280 and 1337. His net worth was around $400 billion. BUSINESS INSTANTLY'.

node.text:
Mansa Musa is regarded as the richest person to ever live...he created this wealth from mining salt, gold deposits, elephant ivory, etc.

He initially inherited a kingdom that was already wealthy, but his work with expanding trade made the kingdom the wealthiest in Africa.

He net worth as been estimated as $400B in today's money, but it's impossible to pin down a number.

Follow us @businessinstantly

node.text:
@bastiaanslot_ has built a 7-figure consulting business from scratch in 2020, and is committed to showing others how they can do the same.

👉🏼Follow @bastiaanslot_
👉🏼Follow @bastiaanslot_

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 7 principles that made me a millionaire in my early 20s. (A thread)'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot Goal setting. If you don't know what you want, then you don't know what to do. Set one clear, tangible goal. Achieve your goal, then repeat.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 2. Sacrifice. If you don't sacrifice for what you want, then your goal becomes the sacrifice.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 3. Health. Sleep wel Eat healthy. Meditate. Exercise. Take time to relax. If you aren't performing at your best, your business won't either.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 4. Gratitude. Always looking to the future future can cause fear, anxiety, and stress. Practice gratitude daily to balance yourself.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 5. Resist impulses. When you're working, resist all urges to eat snacks, grab a treat, or check social media. Train yourself to stay focused on the task at hand, and don't let anything distract you that's how you make progress.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 6. Consistency. Whether you're seeing great results or no results at all, you need to stay consistent. Stay consistent without expecting immediate results. It will all add up long term.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot 7. Invest in yourself. etc. Whether it's books, mentors, seminars, Make sure you're constantly investing in your own growth. You don't have to figure out everything on your own. Find someone who has the results you want and learn from them. That's your "shortcut" to success.'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot Whenever you're feeling stuck or like you're not making progress in life life you can always go back to these principles and see where you're going wrong. |focus on these daily to make sure I stay on track'.

Photo by Business Instantly on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bastiaan Slot @_bastiaanslot If you'd like to see more content and tips abon what learned from building a 7-figure consulting business, drop me a follow.'.

node.text:
Billionaire Warren Buffett has lived in the same house for the past few decades, but still has a vacation house in California.

Buffett was never in this for the luxury items, all he wanted was independence. That's the mindset that will set you apart from becoming rich vs wealthy.

Follow us @businessinstantly

New AI technology is rapidly changing...changing jobs alongside it.

This is why it’s important to build an income for yourself and learn skills that AI can’t replace.

Credit to: @tony.aube.design 
Follow us @businessinstantly

node.text:
Think bigger. You'll see real changes in your bank account and overall life when you begin building and creating. Not by chasing money, but by chasing a real goal...like freedom.

If you want to live a happy life tie it to goals rather than materialistic items.

node.text:
Nas is big into investing in startup companies, or companies just starting out in the stock market. In 2014 he invested $4.5M in Ring and made $40M when Ring sold to Amazon.

This is what sets artists apart from entrepreneurs/investors. Snoop and Nas are making big money because they're diversifying big time.
